<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-06-03T23:29:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-06-03T23:29:00-05:00" n="360" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d360">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 837.00/671.</note>
                        <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-06-03T23:00:00-05:29">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">June</hi> 3, 1912—11 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>A message from the President to Congress to-day asking for authority to
                            suspend constitutional guaranties, in all or part of the Republic as
                            circumstances may demand. Congress to consider matter to-morrow in
                            special session.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Beaupré</hi>.</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>